Software Engineers at 500px create services to solve our technical problems, and develop world-class applications atop our&nbsp;platform.</p>
<p>
Typical challenges include:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Optimizing our system at the application, client, and infrastructure level to deliver results with minimum latency</li>
<li>
Applying machine learning to our data set to help our users better discover beautiful photographs</li>
<li>
Developing algorithms to improve a photograph&#39;s Pulse, based on large numbers of votes and favourites, in real-time</li>
<li>
Architecting our real-time search system to deliver the most relevant results rapidly</li>
<li>
Working with UI/UX Designers to fuse industrial-grade backend services with world-class UIs</li>
</ul>
<p>
We&#39;re looking for people with:</p>
<ul>
<li>
A Bachelors or Masters&nbsp;degree in Computer Science or Engineering (PhDs or PhD dropouts are a bonus)</li>
<li>
Extraordinary software engineering talent</li>
<li>
Knowledge of Ruby, Python, JavaScript and C, or the ability to learn them quickly</li>
<li>
Experience with web applications, databases, distributed systems and machine learning</li>
<li>
A love of photography</li>
</ul>
<p>
Our company has a strong engineering culture, and takes a systems approach to reign in complexity and build robust services.</p>
