			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Linux &mdash;&nbsp;a solid understanding of command line Linux focusing on deb based distributions.</li>
<li>
Networking &mdash;&nbsp;Experience and understanding of networking protocols and troubleshooting.</li>
<li>
Knowledge of, but not limited to, iproute2, pcap, iptables, nginx.</li>
<li>
Databases &mdash; A solid understanding of MySQL and/or MongoDB&nbsp;redundant setups and troubleshooting failures.</li>
<li>
Documentation &mdash; Excellent oral and written English is required.</li>
<li>
Fluent in a technical documentation language, such as Latex, POD, XML, etc.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Test</strong></p>
<p>
Please fill in the following questions to the best of your ability. Be creative and effective.</p>
<p>
<strong>Linux &amp; Networking</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>
Provide two methods of temporarily adding the IP 192.168.32.12/14 to interface tap0.</li>
<li>
An application is failing to start and the log files contain no errors. What steps do you take to troubleshoot the issue?</li>
<li>
You wish to dump an AXFR record to file. How do you go about doing this?</li>
<li>
You have to retrieve the contents of the root crontab files on 192.168.15.2-192.168.15.35. How would you do this?</li>
</ol>
<p>
<strong>Database</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>
A developer comes to you saying that the &quot;photos from new users&quot; page is running slow. He shows you the query that he thinks is responsible. Describe what steps he should take to speed up this query. State all assumptions.</li>
<li>
A developer wants a query that will return the last photo a user took. Assuming that there is a user table and a photo table how would you write the query?</li>
</ol>
<p>
<strong>Documentation</strong> &mdash; please write a document for use by the networking staff to replicate the following install.</p>
<ol>
<li>
Installing MySQL on two servers (ServerA and ServerB)</li>
<li>
Configure ServerA to be a master.</li>
<li>
Configure ServerB to be a slave.</li>
<li>
Create a database containing example data on ServerA.</li>
<li>
Replicate the data on ServerB</li>
<li>
How to verify the setup is functional.</li>
</ol>
]]></description>
