			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Product manager at 500px is responsible for <strong>taking product ideas from concept to delivery</strong>. Product managers will be asked to <strong>organize teams</strong> and schedules to ensure project deadlines are met for web and mobile platforms. This involves <strong>leading small teams</strong>, communicating with the founders, team, business and end-customers, organizing the work, and adhering to the product specifications and deadlines.</p>
<p>
Product managers must be able to <strong>share in the vision of 500px.</strong> Projects are dynamic and require a level of flexibility due to the nature of a maturing startup environment.</p>
<p>
Product Managers must be able to recognize missing competencies in teams and have the ability to identify suitable candidates for both <strong>skills required</strong> and <strong>positive team dynamic</strong>, as such, Product Mangers will be deeply <strong>involved in hiring decisions</strong>.</p>
<p>
Ideal candidates will have <strong>4+ years of product management </strong>experience, coming from <strong>software engineering background</strong> with strong knowledge of RoR, Python, MongoDB, and front-end technologies. The candidate has a <strong>passion for photography</strong> and understands the needs of photographers.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Typical challenges include:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Working with small dynamic team of developers and designers on frequently evolving product</li>
<li>
Adapting and changing the product to the realities of photo-sharing space</li>
<li>
Analyzing and formulating features through communication with founders, customers, and business and technical teams.</li>
<li>
Interacting with hundreds of customers to formulate required features</li>
<li>
Working with team on wireframes and product specification</li>
<li>
Scoping projects accurately and structuring development sprints correctly to keep development teams excited and efficient</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>We are looking for people with:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Strong product manager experience with software engineering background</li>
<li>
Extraordinary communication skills</li>
<li>
Knowledge of Ruby, Python, JavaScript, HAML, SASS, etc.</li>
<li>
Strong knowledge of agile project management software, such as Pivotal Tracker</li>
<li>
Experience of working with several teams on cross-platform features</li>
<li>
A love of photography</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
